'''Yamato Onchi Shrine''' (やまとおんちじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Tenri|Q502196|WD=Q502196|1=Tenri, Nara}}, {{ill|lt=Nara Prefecture|Q131287|WD=Q131287|1=Nara Prefecture}}. It is an {{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|WD=Q11064932|lt=Shikinaisha (small shrine)|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}}, and its former shrine rank was {{ill|lt=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines#Shosha|Q712534|WD=Q712534|lt=village shrine|1=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines}}.

=== History ===
=== Foundation ===
Its foundation is said to date to year 7 of {{ill|lt=Emperor Sujin|Q333530|WD=Q333530|1=Emperor Sujin}}, and the ''Shiki-gunshi'' states that it enshrines the ancestor of the Yamato Onchi clan. The ''{{ill|lt=Shinsen Shōjiroku|Q1045362|WD=Q1045362|1=Shinsen Shōjiroku}}'' records the name "Onchi-no-Miyatsuko" and states: "Yamato no Kambetsu Onchi-no-Miyatsuko are descendants in the 14th generation of Takenori-no-Mikoto, descendant of {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Amatsu-hikone-no-Mikoto|1=UNKNOWN}}." It is inferred that this shrine was where the Yamato Onchi clan enshrined their ancestral deity Takenori-no-Mikoto. There is also {{ill|lt=Onji Shrine|Q11492258|WD=Q11492258|1=Onji Shrine}} (an {{ill|lt=myōjin taisha|Q9610964|WD=Q9610964|1=Myōjin Taisha}} listed in the Engishiki) in {{ill|lt=Yao|Q490872|WD=Q490872|1=Yao, Osaka}}, {{ill|lt=Osaka Prefecture|Q122723|WD=Q122723|1=Osaka Prefecture}} (former {{ill|lt=Kawachi Province|Q1047150|WD=Q1047150|1=Kawachi Province}}), bearing the same "Onchi" name, and a relationship has been suggested; however, that shrine has strong ties with the {{ill|lt=Nakatomi clan|Q1198447|WD=Q1198447|1=Nakatomi clan}}, and its enshrined deity differs from that of this shrine.

=== Chronology ===
*Foundation is given as year 7 of {{ill|lt=Emperor Sujin|Q333530|WD=Q333530|1=Emperor Sujin}}
*{{ill|lt=Ninju|Q1373077|WD=Q1373077|1=Ninju}} 1 ({{ill|lt=851|Q29966|WD=Q29966|1=851}}), 1st month: promoted to Senior Sixth Rank, Upper Grade (''{{ill|lt=Nihon Montoku Tennō Jitsuroku|Q1052905|WD=Q1052905|1=Nihon Montoku Tennō Jitsuroku}}'')
*{{ill|lt=Tengyō|Q1327340|WD=Q1327340|1=Tengyō}} 3 ({{ill|lt=940|Q23830|WD=Q23830|1=940}}), 1st month: rank conferred
*{{ill|lt=Eitoku|Q1145805|WD=Q1145805|1=Eitoku}} 1 ({{ill|lt=1381|Q6331|WD=Q6331|1=1381}}), 2nd month: rank conferred
*{{ill|lt=Shōwa 19|Q5268|WD=Q5268|lt=1944|1=1944}}: relocated to its current site south of the settlement due to plans for construction of the Yamato Naval Air Corps airfield

